Sino-US Relations to Grow on Three Joint Communiques
SAN FRANCISCO , September 20 ( Xinhua ) -- The Sino-U.S. relations will develop further so long as the two countries stick to the three joint communiques and the framework formed by the heads of state of the two countries , a top Chinese military official said here Sunday .
Zhang Wannian , vice chairman of the Central Military Commission of China , made the remarks while meeting with former U.S. defense secretary William Perry at the Stanford University .
During the talks , Zhang praised Perry for what he had done to promote the relationship between the two peoples and military forces of the two countries .
He hoped that U.S. friends , including Perry , would do more in this field .
Zhang arrived in Washington on September 14 for a visit .
